cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Computer Architecture and Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing the runtime performance of a Network-on-Chip (NoC) which is a key component of computer architecture. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper applies reinforcement learning (RL) techniques to optimize NoC runtime performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a system (NoC) through learning and adaptation. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as RL is a subfield of machine learning and neural networks are often used in RL. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a less likely category but still possible as NoCs are a relatively new technology and the paper presents a novel approach to optimizing their performance.
